2 Though dark my path, and sad my lot,
4 Renew my will from day to day;
Let me be still and murmur not,
Blend it with Thine, and take away
Or breathe the prayer divinely taught,
All that now makes it hard to say
3 If Thou shouldst call me to resign
5 Then, when on earth I breathe no more
What most I prize,-it ne'er was mine :
The prayer oft mixed with tears before,
I only yield Thee what is Thine;
I'll sing upon a happier shore,
me kneel - ing, hum bly plead - ing
Thy pres ence, joy and glad - ness

I rejoice to stay by Thee :
See, I yield my life to Thee.
Stoop and raise me, while I praise Thee
For Thy mercy rich and free.
Oh, the richness, oh, the sweetness,
Only good, dear Lord, from Thee,
Help me, Father, help me ever
